result.name: Tung Chung Fort

reviews.text: Amazing historical fort. You can walk round the ramparts
A small fort, historic school with history exhibit
If you love history...is worth it to visit

The best way to get Tung Chung Fort is to take the MTR to Tung Chung and take the bus 11, 34 or 3M. The bus stop is right across. At the entrance is an Indian restaurant. The site is modestly maintained. With all the money the Hong Kong Gov’t has, one would imagine an historical site would be kept in a more dignified condition. But no, the surounding is a dump. You can spend about half an hour at most there. One can always go to the Tung Chung Outlet mall to study the hisory of outlet shopping in Hong Kong. It has more than 10 years of history. Keep remember that the cannons on display are not the originals, but they can give a good idea of what it must've looked like.
Great historical find in Tung Chung. Display of photos and nostalgia on site.

result.adr_address: 香港大嶼山東涌道
result.name: 東涌炮台

reviews.text: 路過就記得行下啦🙏
由東涌消防局走到炮台，需要十五分鐘。炮台內的幾尊大砲及古舊建築物，歴史悠久，值得一看。如果精力充沛，可以沿著石頭路走一圈，回到東涌公立學校，消耗些卡路里，不過要小心，石頭路不是很平坦，最好慢慢行！
有好多大炮,與學校成强烈對比
無甚可睇，只是幾個歷史痕跡，大家如有小孩子的話，都可以帶佢哋一同参觀，解說炮台作用，及以當時香港情況，如去的話，逸東邨向村屋這一邊，好易找到，而大家亦可順带遠足一吓，一條可行沙螺湾大澳，另一條行去寳蓮寺，讓大家除炮台外，可考慮遠足吓，家庭樂外有不同的感受，風景的幽美，係到提一提，沙螺湾較易行D，即衡量孩子們大絪選擇啦！
來東涌看歷史一定要到，如何去呢？先坐港鐵到東涌站，步行至東薈城巴士站轉乘嶼巴38號到北大嶼山醫院站下車，再向馬灣新邨方向步行，再沿東涌道步行10-15分鐘就到。
